
[1]platonic

   PLATON'IC, a. Pertaining to Plato the philosopher, or to his
   philosophy, his school or his opinions.

   Platonic love, is a pure spiritual affection subsisting between the
   sexes, unmixed with carnal desires, and regarding the mind only and its
   excellencies; a species of love for which Plato was a warm advocate.

   Platonic year,the great year, or a period of time determines by the
   revolution of the equinoxes, or the space of time in which the stars
   and constellations return to their former places in respect to the
   equinoxes. This revolution, which is calculated by the precession of
   the equinoxes, is accomplished in about 25,000 years.
